sky.f1.uk.title: F1 2025: The Story So Far
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out for the Canadian Grand Prix as George Russell and Max Verstappen line-up alongside each other at the front with Oscar Piastri in third. Lando Norris comes from P7. (15.06)

sky.f1.uk.title: F1 2025: The Story So Far
sky.f1.uk.description: A McLaren one-two forms the front row for the Australian Grand Prix, as Lando Norris leads from Oscar Piastri. Max Verstappen starts third, while Lewis Hamilton begins from P8. (16.03)

sky.f1.uk.title: F1 2025: The Story So Far
sky.f1.uk.description: It's a first Grand Prix pole for Oscar Piastri as George Russell splits the McLarens with Lando Norris starting third. Sprint winner Lewis Hamilton comes from fifth on the grid. (23.03)

sky.f1.uk.title: F1 2025: The Story So Far
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out at Suzuka for the Japanese Grand Prix. World champion Max Verstappen starts from the front of the grid with the McLaren duo of Lando Norris and Oscar Piastri behind. (06.04)

sky.f1.uk.title: F1 2025: The Story So Far
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out for the 2025 Bahrain Grand Prix. Oscar Piastri holds pole position with his McLaren teammate Lando Norris down in P6. Charles Leclerc joins Piastri on the front row. (13.04)

sky.f1.uk.title: F1 2025: The Story So Far
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out in Jeddah for the 2025 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix. Reigning world champion Max Verstappen crossed the finish line in P1 last season at the Jeddah Corniche Circuit. (20.04)

sky.f1.uk.title: F1 2025: The Story So Far
sky.f1.uk.description: Polesitter Max Verstappen is joined by Lando Norris and Kimi Antonelli heading into turn one, while Lewis Hamilton tries to fight through the field from P12. (04.05)

sky.f1.uk.title: F1 2025: The Story So Far
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out at Imola for the 2025 Emilia Romagna Grand Prix. Last season, reigning world champion Max Verstappen held off a late Lando Norris charge to claim race victory. (18.05)

sky.f1.uk.title: F1 2025: The Story So Far

UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Andrew 'Freddie' Flintoff presents the action-packed show in which 24 brave contestants take on a series of challenging water-based inflatable games and obstacles. S1 Ep1

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Border Force America's Gatekeepers
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: A new recruit fresh out of training school makes her mark when she uncovers 12kg of cocaine hidden in a car that she has stopped on one of the bridges. S1 Ep9

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Border Force America's Gatekeepers
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Customs and Border Protection officers think they spot a trend when they seize drugs from behind the dashboards of two cars. S1 Ep10

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Cape Carnage: Killer Catch
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: New Blood in the Dory: The crew of the Wildcard battle sharks, a giant crocodile, chronic injury, arguments and persistent fog that all threaten to derail their season target and pay. S1 Ep9

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Cape Carnage: Killer Catch
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: The Final Assault: The Wildcard's crew are just over two tonnes short of their 45-tonne goal as they fight for their last chance at a killer catch at Cape Carnage with sharks circling. S1 Ep10

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Celebrity Storage Hunters
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Ropley: Joe Wilkinson, Ulrika Jonsson, Mark Watson and Jenny Eclair are amongst the A-list auction hunters that Sean Kelly has to rein in, as more celebs haggle for storage lots. S1 Ep2

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Celebrity Storage Hunters
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Lewes: A-list auction anarchy as Vic and Bob, Theo Paphitis, Janet Street Porter, Stephen K Amos and Phil Tufnell scrap for storage lots, turning any profit over to charity. S1 Ep3

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Extreme Salvage Squad
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Luke and his team are contracted to remove two stolen vehicles from an abandoned mine site that has been turned into a recreational lake for weekend campers and water skiers. S2 Ep2

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Top Gear
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: The lads race round Donington in three stripped-out cars: the KTM X-Bow, the Morgan Three Wheeler and the Caterham R500. S18 Ep6

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Top Gear
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: A good drive spoiled? Jeremy, Richard and James find out if you can go motor racing for less than it costs to play golf, and rock icon Slash is let loose in a Reasonably Priced Car. S18 Ep7

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Hairy Bikers' Best of British
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Pork: The Bikers celebrate the British love affair with pork as they prepare a traditional gala pie and a sumptuous rolled pork loin with apricots and ginger. S2 Ep6

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Rick Stein's Taste of Shanghai
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Rick Stein explores the food of Shanghai - Shanghai is one of the biggest cities in the world and is rapidly expanding, but has it hung on to its culinary roots?

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Would I Lie To You?
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Rob Brydon, Lee Mack and David Mitchell are joined by Bob Mortimer, Samantha Morton, Miles Jupp and Sarah Hadland. S14 Ep4

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Richard Osman's House of Games
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Snooker legend Dennis Taylor aims to rack up success when he takes on comedians Yasmine Akram, Cariad Lloyd, and Geoff Norcott in Richard's quizzing showdown this time. S5 Ep35

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Richard Osman's House of Games
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Former British Olympian Roger Black joins comedians Jo Brand, Sanjeev Kohli, and Tiff Stevenson in a race to test their general knowledge against Richard's cunning challenges. S5 Ep40

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: QI XL
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Medieval and Macabre: Enlightenment on the Middle Ages with Stephen Fry. Julia Zemiro, Matt Lucas, David Mitchell and Alan Davies hear that pre-fabs date to pre-Ikea times! S13 Ep12

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Have I Got a Bit More News for You
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: David Dimbleby hosts an extended edition of the satirical quiz, with Stacey Dooley and Henning Wehn joining team captains Ian Hislop and Paul Merton. S57 Ep1

E4Plus1.uk.description: The Citation Negation: Sheldon and Amy get some devastating news. Bernadette asks Stuart's girlfriend Denise to teach her how to beat Howard at a video game. (S12 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The VCR Illumination: Sheldon and Amy are still upset about their theory being disproven, but a video tape from Sheldon's past inspires him not to give up. (S12 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Paintball Scattering: Jealousy, trust issues and tension among the couples in the gang cause mayhem when Penny and Leonard organise a paintball game. (S12 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Dear Beloved Family: Gloria rushes Phil to hospital for emergency surgery when he experiences intense stomach pains. (S9 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to the Wagon: Dave and Tina discover a common bond when they go to a concert together. (S2 Ep6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Lake Life: Jay makes the family take their holiday on a houseboat to create memories that will last long after he's gone. And Mitchell runs into an old flame. (S9 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Long Goodbye: Phil and Claire realise that Alex is more self-sufficient in college than they thought. Manny is determined to avoid a tearful goodbye when he moves to college. (S9 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Rude(ish) Tube Shorts
E4Plus1.uk.description: A short, cheeky clip featuring animals and food, from the always hilarious Tube that is Rude.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Revisit 2: Gordon Ramsay revisits four restaurants he tried to help: the Spanish Pavillion in New Jersey, and Kingston Café, La Frite and Capri in California. (S5 Ep17) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: La Galleria 33 (Part 1/2): Gordon tries to help La Galleria 33, run by sisters Rita and Lisa, who blame the restaurant's failures on everything from tablecloths to the weather. (S6 Ep1) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Left Behind: Flanders loses his job and comes to work with Homer at the power plant. Homer prays for him to be fired. (S29 Ep19/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Throw Grampa from the Dane: The Simpsons visit Denmark and all fall in love with it - except Homer. Meanwhile, Grampa needs a serious operation. (S29 Ep20/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Clean Room Infiltration: Amy hosts a Victorian Christmas Eve dinner, complete with party games. Raj, Leonard and Howard have pigeon problems. (S8 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Space Probe Disintegration: Howard tries to calm a stressed Raj, who is anxiously awaiting the arrival of some data from a space probe that he helped launch. (S8 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: When a Tree Falls: Mitch helps Cam to save an old tree in the park, while Jay and Manny go beyond their comfort zones at a kid's Olympics-themed birthday party. (S4 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Diamond in the Rough: When Manny and Luke's little league team unexpectedly makes it into a playoff game, Claire and Cameron scramble to find a location for it. (S4 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Novelization Correlation: Amy appears on the Professor Proton show. Penny hates the idea that the female protagonist in Leonard's novel is based on her. (S11 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Neonatal Nomenclature: Bernadette's friends try various tactics to help her go into labour. (S11 Ep16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Athenaeum Allocation: Leonard jumps through hoops to secure the perfect wedding venue for Sheldon and Amy. Howard and Bernadette face a big decision. (S11 Ep17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Gates Excitation: The guys do everything in their power to meet Bill Gates when his firm has dealings with the pharmaceutical company Penny works for. (S11 Ep18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
E4Plus1.uk.description: Valloweaster: It's heist time. The squad compete for the title of the greatest human/genius. (S7 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
E4Plus1.uk.description: Ransom: Holt asks for Jake's help in a case that's exceptionally meaningful to him. Charles and Terry work together on a side business. (S7 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Dad-Feelings Limited: As Comic Book Guy and his wife Kumiko debate whether to have a baby, his awesome origin story is revealed. (S32 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Diary Queen: Bart finds his old teacher's diary and learns a surprising secret. Then Lisa discovers an even bigger surprise. (S32 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Propagation Proposition: Penny's ex-boyfriend Zack and his wife want a baby, but when they encounter fertility problems, they ask Leonard for his help. (S12 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Confirmation Polarization: Sheldon and Amy are thrilled when their super-asymmetry theory is proved correct. Bernadette enjoys some big success at work. (S12 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Meteorite Manifestation: Sheldon is thrilled to help Howard and Bernadette with some bureaucratic paperwork, until he realises that they're breaking the law. (S12 Ep14)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Donation Oscillation: Penny attempts to sabotage Leonard's efforts to help her ex-boyfriend Zack and his wife Marissa have a family of their own. (S12 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Rome-Old & Juli-eh: Homer stops paying for Grampa's retirement home, so he has to stay with the family instead. In a twist no one saw coming, Grampa ends up marrying Selma. (S18 Ep15/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Homerazzi: Homer becomes a paparazzo to get money to pay for fire damage to the house. But Springfield's celebrities are alarmed by his aggressive style and fight back. (S18 Ep16/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Musk Who Fell to Earth: Elon Musk turns up in Springfield, befriends Homer and revolutionises the nuclear power plant - which costs Mr Burns dearly... (S26 Ep12/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: Hollyoaks Does Come Dine
E4Plus1.uk.description: with Me: Brand new series: Charlie Wernham hosts an East End night, in a portable kitchen, on the Hollyoaks set! Let's hope his seafood isn't damp squib! And who's won the week? (Ep5/5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Treehouse of Horror VII: It's Halloween! Settle down for a night of Springfield spookiness. Bart finds his evil twin in the attic, and Lisa becomes God to a race of tiny people. (S8 Ep1/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Treehouse of Horror XVI: The Homer-fied horror continues. Bart is replaced by a well-behaved robot. Homer takes part in a deadly TV show. Lisa turns into Albert Einstein. (S17 Ep4/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Treehouse of Horror XIX: The sinister Simpsons action continues. Homer encounters a murderous rigged voting machine. Lisa's toy car and a vengeful pumpkin get a bit deadly too. (S20 Ep4/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Treehouse of Horror XXII: It's no trick - we're treating you to more scary Simpsons. Homer is paralysed by a spider, and Flanders is transformed into a cold-blooded vigilante. (S23 Ep3/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Treehouse of Horror XXV: The spine-chilling Springfieldian stories continue, with Bart and Lisa in an evil alternate universe, and Moe's terrifying Clockwork Orange-style gang. (S26 Ep4/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Treehouse of Horror XXVIII: Get your head out of the apple bobbing bucket and in front of E4, as the Simpsons become Halloween candy, and Maggie needs an exorcism. (S29 Ep4/21)

Film4.uk.title: Where the Crawdads Sing
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Daisy Edgar-Jones stars in director Olivia Newman's adaptation of Delia Owens' best-selling novel about a feral child who's accused of murder in America's Deep South. Did she do it?

Film4.uk.title: The Night House
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Supernatural horror with Rebecca Hall. A woman starts to think her dead husband is haunting her as she wrestles with her grief in the isolated lakeside house he built for them.

Film4.uk.title: Pig
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Thriller. Nicolas Cage delivers a subtle turn in Michael Sarnoski's debut, an intriguing tale of an off-the-grid truffle hunter who returns to the city to rescue his kidnapped pig.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Father Brown
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Crime-comedy starring Alec Guinness. A priest is tasked with accompanying a priceless religious artifact from London to Rome. But the prolific thief Flambeau is hot on his trail...

Film4.uk.title: Three Hours to Kill
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Western starring Dana Andrews. A man falsely accused of murder gets a last-minute reprieve from the lynch mob so he can track down the real culprit.

Film4.uk.title: Mandy
Film4.uk.description: (1952) Poignant Ealing drama starring seven-year-old Mandy Miller as a deaf girl whose parents - played by Phyllis Calvert and Terence Morgan - fight over her treatment.

Film4.uk.title: Nicholas Nickleby
Film4.uk.description: (1947) Drama with Derek Bond, based on Charles Dickens' novel. After his father dies, Nicholas seeks the help of his cold, avaricious, scheming uncle. Predictably, it doesn't go well.

Film4.uk.title: First Knight
Film4.uk.description: (1995) Romantic drama based on Arthurian legend, starring Richard Gere, Sean Connery and Julia Ormond. Can nomadic swordsman Lancelot contain his love for King Arthur's fiancée?

Film4.uk.title: Late Night with the Devil
Film4.uk.description: (2023) Unsettling found-footage horror with David Dastmalchian. A has-been host tries to save his 70s talk show using a demonically possessed 13-year-old girl. Really, what could go wrong?

Film4.uk.title: Angel Has Fallen
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Action-thriller sequel. Secret agent Mike Banning (Gerard Butler) goes on the run when he's framed for an attack on the President. Can he clear his name?

Film4.uk.title: Isolation
Film4.uk.description: (2005) Gory horror with John Lynch, Essie Davis and Sean Harris. Biotech experiments bring bloody mayhem to a struggling Irish dairy farm.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Siege at Red River
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Western. Van Johnson stars as a Confederate agent who steals a Gatling gun prototype from the Yankees and attempts to smuggle it south through enemy lines to his own side.

Film4.uk.title: The Enemy Below
Film4.uk.description: (1957) Second World War thriller. Robert Mitchum stars as the captain of a US destroyer in the North Atlantic hunting down a German U-boat and its world-weary captain, Curt Jurgens.

Film4.uk.title: The Colditz Story
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Classic Second World War drama. John Mills, Lionel Jeffries and Bryan Forbes star as just some of the POWs determined to break out of the infamous German 'escape-proof' prison.

Film4.uk.title: Jubal
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Western with Glenn Ford, Ernest Borgnine, Rod Steiger and Valerie French. A cowboy is given a job by a rancher, sparking lethal jealousy in a colleague and desire in the boss's wife.

Film4.uk.title: Sister Act 2: Back in the Habit
Film4.uk.description: (1993) Comedy sequel starring Whoopi Goldberg and Lauryn Hill. Deloris - who's now made it big in Vegas - goes back undercover as a teacher to help a struggling school choir find its voice.

Film4.uk.title: Copshop
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Action thriller with Gerard Butler. A hitman gets himself arrested so that he can get to a bad guy, who also got himself arrested, so that he could hide from the hitman.

Film4.uk.title: Alita: Battle Angel
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Partially animated action film based on a popular manga comic. Alita, a deadly cyborg brought back to life by a mourning scientist, sets out to discover her true identity.

Film4.uk.title: Corpus Christi
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Crime drama. A young ex-con wants to be a priest so much that he pretends to be one. But trouble soon finds him. In Polish/subs. Strong language/violence/sex/drugs.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: The Man Between
Film4.uk.description: (1953) Atmospheric thriller set in post-war Berlin, where Ivo Kern (James Mason) and Susanne Mallison (Claire Bloom) get caught up in a maelstrom of bigamy, blackmail and bullets.

Film4.uk.title: Gideon of Scotland Yard
Film4.uk.description: (1958) Drama. Jack Hawkins stars as Police Inspector Gideon, who faces outrage and danger in his quest to bring London's criminals to justice. With Anna Massey, John Loder and Cyril Cusack.

Film4.uk.title: Footsteps in the Fog
Film4.uk.description: (1955) Atmospheric Victorian melodrama. Stewart Granger plays a sinister aristocrat who poisons his wife. However, his maid (Jean Simmons) knows his secret and tries to use it against him.

Film4.uk.title: Dead of Night
Film4.uk.description: (1945) Five uncanny tales of the supernatural in one eerie package, the most famous starring ventriloquist Michael Redgrave and a deadly dummy. Prepare to be spooked.
